    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Lithuania/14</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 78</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your despatch No. 1275 of
                    September 15, 1923, regarding the indebtedness of Lithuania to the United States
                    and the opinions of Dr. Narushkevich reported therein, you are instructed to
                    take the first suitable opportunity to inform Dr. Narushkevich, or the
                    appropriate official of the Lithuanian Government, that the Government of the
                    United States is not aware of any understanding with the Lithuanian Government
                    that repayment of Lithuania’s indebtedness to the United States would not be
                    asked until Lithuania had received its reparation payments.</p>
                <p>In accordance with your request a photostat copy of each of the four obligations
                    of the Government of Lithuania held by the United States Treasury is
                        enclosed.<note n="8" xml:id="d163fn8">Not reproduced.</note> These
                    obligations are as follows: <table cols="3" rend="width: 85%;"
                        rendition="#center-block" rows="6">
                        <row>
                            <cell cols="2">Date of obligation</cell>
                            <cell>Principal sum</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell role="num">June 28,</cell>
                            <cell>1919,</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$4,159,491.96</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell role="num">June 30,</cell>
                            <cell>”</cell>
                            <cell role="num">306,433.00</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell role="num">June 30,</cell>
                            <cell>”</cell>
                            <cell role="num">84,536.07</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell role="num">June 30,</cell>
                            <cell>”</cell>
                            <cell role="num">431,167.00</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Total:</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#underline" role="num">$4,981,628.03</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
